messageShortText: Transfer failed for order plan item: product &1, location &2, run ID &3
diagnosis: An error occurred while transferring the order plan item to the destination system. As a result, the transfer could not be completed, and no order list item was created for the order plan item in the destination system.
procedure: Check the Details area for more information about the cause of the exception. The exception can be caused by the following errors: - Low level message 101 (Mapping error in the receiving system; check application log): An error occurred in the receiving system while processing order plan items. The affected order plan items were set to the Transfer for Purchase Order Creation Failed status. For more detailed information about the underlying error, check the receiving system's application log (transaction SLG1) for the object RFM_XRP_ORDERPLAN. - Low level message 102 (Error while calling the destination): A connection to the destination system could not be established. - Low level message 103 (Order plan item could not be locked; foreign lock exists): The order plan item could not be locked, because it is locked by another process. - Low level message 104 (Order plan item could not be locked; internal error from enqueue server): The order plan item could not be locked, because an error occurred on the enqueue server. After correcting the cause of the error, retransfer the order plan items concerned.
comments: low level message 101 usually appears if the order plan item is obsolete when transfering it into ERP system:  message RFM_XRP 102 in object RFM_XRP_ORDERPLAN refers to object MMPUR_RPO  with message text "Item with hash key 1006 | <material nb> | <date> <time> and material <nb> for purchase order  is obsolete". The order date/time already is in the past and not within the configured order buffer time in ERP customizing in Materials Management > Purchasing > Order Optimizing > Grouping of Order List Items into Purchase Orders > Define Control Characteristics. The order buffer time cannot be higher than 60 minutes.
referredConfiguration: ERP customizing: Diverse customizing in section Materials Management > Purchasing > Order Optimizing > Grouping of Order List Items into Purchase Orders. See SAP Help Portal: https://help.sap.com/viewer/ab9f80a058f54408b2a7b1269d759b38/latest/en-US/cc3dc63f86e741b6ad11d432bd7cb685.html

Invalid unit of measure; stock could not be determined
diagnosis: The stock data available for the requested product location is not in the base unit of measure or the stock data for different segments of the product location is in different units of measure.
systemResponse: Stock quantity cannot be determined.
procedure: Check and correct the data. The DDF stock must be stored in the base unit of measure.

messageShortText: Different stock update dates/times for segments
diagnosis: The stock data for different segments of a product location is updated at different points in time.
systemResponse: The most current update date/time is considered for the aggregated stock.

messageShortText: No stock data found
diagnosis: There is no stock data available for the requested product location.
systemResponse: Stock quantity cannot be determined.
procedure: Maintain the stock data.

messageShortText: Real-time inventory data not found
diagnosis: Real-time inventory data for the requested product location is not available.
systemResponse: The system cannot determine the quantity of real-time inventory and will use the inventory data replicated from the master data system for the calculation.
procedure: Enable the use of real-time inventory for the product location.

messageShortText: Customer-specific stock determination failed with error code &1
diagnosis: An error occurred while determining customer-specific stock. Detailed explanations of the underlying error and possible actions to resolve it can be defined by the customer. This text should never be changed by SAP to avoid overwriting the customer-defined explanation.

messageShortText: Customer-specific stock determination led to warning with error code &1
diagnosis: An error occurred while determining customer-specific stock which leads to a warning. Detailed explanations of the underlying error and possible actions to resolve it can be defined by the customer. This text should never be changed by SAP to avoid overwriting the customer-defined explanation.

messageShortText: Order unit could not be determined
diagnosis: There could no valid order unit be determined from the transportation lane, and no base unit of measure is defined for the selected product, or there is a default order unit defined but no conversion factors are available.
systemResponse: No valid order unit could be determined.
procedure: Check and correct the data.

messageShortText: Invalid conversion factors for order unit &1 from info record lane
diagnosis: The order unit that has been determined from the transportation lane with the source of supply type "Info Record" has invalid conversion factors.
systemResponse: The order unit cannot be used. The service follows up on the determination logic to determine a valid order unit.
procedure: Check and correct the data.

messageShortText: Invalid conversion factors for issue unit &1 from supplying site lane
diagnosis: The issue unit that has been determined from the transportation lane with the source of supply type "Supplying Site" has invalid conversion factors.
systemResponse: The issue unit cannot be used. The service follows up on the determination logic to determine a valid order unit.
procedure: Check and correct the data.

messageShortText: Order unit &1 could not be used
diagnosis: The imported order unit is no valid order unit and cannot be used.
systemResponse: No valid order unit could be determined.
procedure: Check and correct the data.

messageShortText: Invalid conversion factors for default order unit &1
diagnosis: The default order unit defined for the selected product has invalid conversion factors.
systemResponse: The default order unit cannot be used. The service follows up on the determination logic to determine a valid order unit.
procedure: Check and correct the data.

messageShortText: No valid variable order unit setting for lane available; default used
diagnosis: The variable order unit setting assigned to the selected transportation lane is not a valid variable order unit setting.
systemResponse: As fallback, variable order units are only determined for rounding.
procedure: Check and correct the variable order unit setting in the transportation lane master data. If no valid value is available in the transportation lane data from ERP, make sure that the relevant data is provided.

messageShortText: No valid variable order unit setting for product available; default used
diagnosis: The variable order unit setting assigned to the selected product is not a valid variable order unit setting.
systemResponse: As fallback, variable order units are only determined for rounding.
procedure: Check and correct the variable order unit setting in the product master data. If no valid value is available in the product data from ERP, make sure that the relevant data is provided.

messageShortText: Rounding profile &1 from transp. lane not available; assignment ignored
diagnosis: The rounding profile assigned to the selected transportation lane is not available in DDF.
systemResponse: The rounding profile assignment is ignored. If the rounding profile from the receiving location product is to be considered as defined in Customizing, it is determined.
procedure: Check and correct the rounding profile in the transportation lane master data. If no rounding settings from ERP are available, make sure that the relevant data is provided. Caution: Not all rounding profiles from ERP can be transferred to and used in DDF. Only profiles with dynamic rounding rules are applicable.

messageShortText: Rounding profile &1 from prod.rec.loc. not available; assignment ignored
diagnosis: The rounding profile assigned to the selected product location is not available in DDF.
systemResponse: The rounding profile assignment is ignored. If the rounding profile from another level is to be considered as defined in Customizing, it is determined.
procedure: Check and correct the rounding profile in the product location master data. If no rounding settings from ERP are available, make sure that the required data is provided. Caution: not all rounding profiles from ERP can be transferred to and used in DDF. Only profiles with dynamic rounding rules are applicable.

messageShortText: UoM group &1 from prod.loc. not available; assignment ignored
diagnosis: The unit of measure group assigned to the selected product location is not available in DDF.
systemResponse: The unit of measure group assignment is ignored.
procedure: Check and correct the unit of measure group in the product location master data. If no unit of measure group settings from ERP are available, make sure that the required data is provided.

messageShortText: Rounding profile &1 from prod.sup.loc. not available; assignment ignored
diagnosis: The rounding profile assigned to the selected product in the supplying location is not available in DDF.
systemResponse: The rounding profile assignment is ignored. If the rounding profile from another level is to be considered as defined Customizing, it is determined.
procedure: Check and correct the rounding profile in the product location master data. If no rounding settings from ERP are available, make sure that the required data is provided. Caution: not all rounding profiles from ERP can be transferred to and used in DDF. Only profiles with dynamic rounding rules are applicable.

messageShortText: UoM group &1 from transp. lane not available; assignment ignored
diagnosis: The unit of measure group assigned to the transportation lane is not available in DDF.
systemResponse: The assignment is ignored.
procedure: Check and correct the unit of measure group in the transportation lane. If no unit of measure group settings from ERP are available, make sure that the relevant data is provided.

messageShortText: UoM group &1 from prod.sup.loc. not available; assignment ignored
diagnosis: The unit of measure group assigned to the product and supplying location is not available in DDF.
systemResponse: The assignment is ignored.
procedure: Check and correct the unit of measure group that is assigned to the product and supplying location master data. If no unit of measure group settings from ERP are available, make sure that the relevant data is provided.

messageShortText: Open goods movement from PO &1&2&3 not considered; no conversion factors
diagnosis: There is a purchase order available to be considered as open goods movement for the product location, but it is not in the base unit of measure. There are no conversion factors available to calculate the open quantity in the base unit of measure.
systemResponse: The purchase order is not considered as open goods movement.
procedure: Check and correct the purchase order data.

messageShortText: Open goods movement from order plan item not considered; invalid UOM &1
diagnosis: There is an order plan item available to be considered as open goods movement for the product location, but it is not in the base unit of measure. There are no conversion factors available to calculate the open quantity in the base unit of measure.
systemResponse: The order plan item is not considered as open goods movement.
procedure: Maintain the required conversion factors for the product location.

messageShortText: Enter a replenishment type
Replenishment type &1 is not valid
diagnosis: You have entered a replenishment type that is not defined as a valid replenishment type.
systemResponse: The replenishment type cannot be defined as relevant for replenishment planning.
procedure: Select a valid replenishment type, or maintain the entered replenishment type in Customizing for Demand Data Foundation first.

messageShortText: OP Item to be updated does not exist
Mapping error in the receiving system &1; check application log
diagnosis: An error occurred in the receiving system while processing order plan items. The affected order plan items were set to the Transfer for Purchase Order Creation Failed status. For more detailed information about the underlying error, check the receiving system's application log (transaction SLG1) for the object RFM_XRP_ORDERPLAN.
procedure: Correct the cause of the error and retransfer the order plan items concerned.

messageShortText: Error while calling the destination &1.
diagnosis: A connection to the destination system could not be established.
procedure: Correct the cause of the error and retransfer the order plan items concerned.

messageShortText: Order plan item could not be locked; foreign lock exists
diagnosis: The order plan item could not be locked, because it is locked by another process.
procedure: Retransfer the order plan item concerned when it has been unlocked.

messageShortText: Order plan item could not be locked; internal error from enqueue server
diagnosis: The order plan item could not be locked, because an error occurred on the enqueue server.
procedure: Correct the cause of the error and retransfer the order plan item concerned.

messageShortText: Status update failed; status &1 could not be set
diagnosis: A technical error occurred during order plan outbound processing.
systemResponse: The status of the order plan item could not be updated. The order plan outbound processing stopped.
procedure: Depending on the status that could not be set, follow these steps: •Target status 45 "Transfer for Purchase Order Creation in Progress": Order plan outbound processing stopped before the data could be transferred for purchase order creation. The application log contains information about the root cause of the error. You can reschedule the order plan transfer. •Target status 40 "Transfer for Purchase Order Creation Failed": The order plan item could not be transferred to an ERP system successfully and its status could not be updated accordingly. The order plan item retains the status 45 "Transfer for Purchase Order Creation in Progress" until the status is manually corrected. •Target status 50 "Transferred for Purchase Order Creation": The order plan item was successfully transferred to an ERP system, but the status could not be updated accordingly. The order plan item retains the status 45 "Transfer for Purchase Order Creation in Progress" until the status is manually corrected.

messageShortText: No procurement schedule assignment exists
diagnosis: No procurement schedule is assigned to the product location.
systemResponse: No replenishment schedule is determined for the product location.
procedure: Assign a procurement schedule to the product location.

messageShortText: No or invalid time zone defined for the receiving location
diagnosis: There is no time zone defined for the receiving location or the defined time zone is invalid.
systemResponse: The dates and times defined for the procurement schedule items are considered to be in UTC. They do not refer to the time zone of the assigned receiving location.
procedure: Maintain or correct the time zone of the receiving location.

messageShortText: Number of additional dates/times cannot be included in the repl. schedule
diagnosis: By providing a positive number of additional dates and times, you requested procurement schedule items to be included in the replenishment schedule, in addition to those requested due to the selected order time frame. The number of additionally requested procurement schedule items could not or not completely be included in the replenishment schedule, because there are not enough procurement schedule items available beyond the selected order time range in the procurement schedule assigned to the product location.
systemResponse: No or not all additionally requested procurement schedule items are included in the replenishment schedule.
comments: Replenishment calculation has been executed for a period for which at least one order date/time within the period has no subsequent order date/time after end of the horizon. The exception is created on product location level and therefore does not mean, that the relevant OPI has an insufficient procurement schedule, but it was not possible to calculate OPI for the complete order horizon as requested.

messageShortText: The procurement schedule with UUID &1 does not exist
diagnosis: The procurement schedule used for the product location does not exist.
systemResponse: No replenishment schedule is determined.
procedure: Enter an existing procurement schedule.

messageShortText: The calculated staging date/time is set to the delivery date/time
diagnosis: The staging date and time was calculated by adding the goods issue processing time of the product in the supplying location to the order date and time of the procurement schedule item. The resulting staging date and time is greater than the delivery date and time.
systemResponse: Since the staging date and time cannot be greater than the delivery date and time, the staging date and time was set to the delivery date and time.

messageShortText: The staging date/time is set to the order date/time
diagnosis: The staging date and time could not be calculated by adding the goods issue processing time of the product in the supplying location to the order date and time of the procurement schedule item because no supplying location could be determined.
systemResponse: The staging date and time is set to the order date and time.

messageShortText: Gap in time-dependent procurement schedule assignment
diagnosis: Within the time range considered for the determination of a replenishment schedule, there is a gap of dates and times in which no procurement schedule is assigned to the product location.
systemResponse: The system ignores the dates and times within the gap, and only considers the dates and times for which a procurement schedule assignment exists for the determination of a replenishment schedule.
procedure: Check the procurement schedule assignment for the product location for all dates and times within the considered time range.

messageShortText: Goods receipts docs from PO &1&2 not considered. No conversion factors
diagnosis: There are goods receipts documents linked to the purchase order item which do not specify the quantity in the base unit of measure. The conversion of the posted quantity to the base unit of measure is not possible since there are no conversion factors available in the purchase order item.
systemResponse: These goods receipts documents are not considered for the calculation of the shelf life distribution of the start stock.
procedure: Check and correct the conversion factors of the purchase order data.

messageShortText: Goods receipts docs from PO &1&2 not considered. Inconsistent unit
diagnosis: There are goods receipts documents linked to the purchase order item which specify the quantity in another unit of measure than defined in the purchase order item. This prevents a conversion of the posted quantity to the base unit of measure.
systemResponse: These goods receipts documents are not considered for the calculation of the shelf life distribution of the start stock.
procedure: Check and correct the unit of measure of the purchase order data or the goods receipt document data.

messageShortText: Goods receipts docs from PO &1&2 not considered. PO is goods issue
diagnosis: There are goods receipts documents linked to the purchase order item that is defined as a goods issue. Since goods issues are not part of the stock, they are not considered for the calculation of the shelf life distribution of the current stock.
systemResponse: These goods receipts documents are not considered for the shelf life distribution of the start stock.
procedure: Check and correct the flag IS_RETURNS in the purchase order data.

messageShortText: No operating times defined for the receiving location
diagnosis: There are no operating times defined for any weekday in the master data of the receiving location.
systemResponse: The determination of operating times does not return any data.
procedure: Define the operating times in the master data of the receiving location.

Runtime error in replenishment calculation
diagnosis: This error occurs when something unspecified went wrong during replenishment calculation.
systemResponse: Runtime error in replenishment calculation.
procedure: Please contact your system administrator.

messageShortText: Unable to generate replenishment run ID, number range object &1, error &2
diagnosis: Retrieval of a number from the number range object &1 failed.
systemResponse: The following error codes are returned from the used function module NUMBER_GET_NEXT: 1: interval not found 2: number range not intern 3: object not found 4: quantity is 0 5: quantity is not 1 6: interval overflow 7: buffer overflow 8: OTHERS
procedure: Contact the person who is responsible for the Customizing of your system. In case of error code 1 (interval not found), set up the number range interval for number range object &1 in Customizing under Maintain Number Range for Replenishment Run ID. For other error codes, please refer to the documentation of function module NUMBER_GET_NEXT.

Look into the explanation of the existing exceptions and use the information therein to resolve the underlying issue.

systemResponse: For a certain order date time, no order plan item could be generated for one or more product locations.
procedure: Try to resolve the issue based on the exception details. If in doubt, contact SAP support.

systemResponse: For each group of exceptions with the same details, only one application log entry has been created. By doing so, &1 entries were suppressed.

messageShortText: Minimum service level underrun for order quantity. Target &1% actual &2%
diagnosis: No order candidate fulfills the configured minimum service level constraint because no order candidate has a higher service level than . The replenishment calculation has determined an order quantity that yields a service level of .
systemResponse: The replenishment calculation selects an order quantity based on other defined constraints and the configured cost model.
procedure: When the resulting order quantity does not meet your business needs and an urgent action is required adapt the order quantity in the Review Order Plan Items app. Fix the root cause behind any data-related warnings that are displayed for this order plan item in the Review Order Plan Items app. The replenishment calculation determines only an order quantity that fulfills a minimum service level if the probability of out-of-stock situations is reduced: •Use the Simulate Replenishment app to find unusual quantities within the timeseries of different KPIs. •Parameterize the replenishment calculation in a way that avoids large quantities of lost sales or spoilage. •The frequency of order dates and times in the procurement schedule also influences lost sales or spoilage and thus the risk of violating the minimum service level. This especially holds true for products with a short shelf life.

messageShortText: Max range of coverage overrun for order quantity. Target &1d actual &2d
diagnosis: No order candidate fulfills the configured maximum range of coverage constraint, because no order candidate has a lower range of coverage than  days. The replenishment calculation has chosen an order quantity that yields a range of coverage of  days.
systemResponse: The replenishment calculation selects an order quantity based on other defined constraints and the configured cost model.
procedure: If the resulting order quantity does not meet your business needs and an urgent action is required, adapt the order quantity in the Review Order Plan Items app. Fix the root cause behind any data-related warnings that are displayed for this order plan item in the Review Order Plan Items app. The replenishment calculation only determines an order quantity that fulfills a maximum range of coverage if the remaining stock is not too high at the delivery date and time of the follow-on order. Therefore, consider the following: •Use the Simulate Replenishment app to find unusual quantities within the timeseries of different KPIs. •Parameterize the replenishment calculation in a way that avoids high quantities of stock. •A high range of coverage might also be caused by an unusual decrease of demand for the time period after the follow-on order’s delivery.

messageShortText: No order quantity for order &1 delivery &2. Error or unsupported input
diagnosis: The replenishment calculation failed to calculate an order plan item for the given order date/time and delivery date/time. This happens when a technical error occurred, or a calculation step was provided with data that it cannot process.
systemResponse: The replenishment calculation cannot determine an order quantity and thus not create the order plan item. Any comparable order plan item that originates from a previous replenishment run is kept in the system. The replenishment calculation cannot calculate any order plan item for the given product and receiving location that has the order date/time after this order plan item.
procedure: Inspect the low level exceptions attached to this high level exception to retrieve further information about the potential root cause. Fix the root cause behind any other data-related errors or warnings that are generated for this replenishment run. To inspect other exceptions that have been detected during this replenishment run you can use the Monitor Exceptions service. Exceptions that cannot be associated with a calculated order plan item are by default assigned to Business Area Replenishment Cause Determination. For further information on how to filter exceptions by Business Area see the Monitor Exceptions section in the application help for SAP Customer Activity Repository. If the low level exceptions or any other exceptions generated for this replenishment run do not allow you to find the root cause, please reach out to SAP.

messageShortText: Unreliable schedule data for receiving location
diagnosis: The replenishment calculation detected inconsistent or unusual data regarding the procurement schedule. This affects all order plan items for the associated receiving location. Depending on the kind of data issue this might also lead to some order plan items not being calculated successfully.
systemResponse: The replenishment calculation attempts to create the order plan items anyway, making assumptions where required. When the calculation of an affected order plan item succeeds, certain order plan items are overwritten. The overwriting applies to order plan items for a particular product location originating from a previous replenishment run and whose order dates and times are at or after the beginning of the planning horizon.
procedure: When the resulting order quantities do not meet your business needs and an urgent action is required, adapt the order quantities in the Review Order Plan Items app. Fix the root cause behind this data-related warning. Inspect the low level exceptions attached to this high level exception to retrieve further information about the potential root cause.

messageShortText: Replenishment calculation aborted. Failed to read schedule
diagnosis: The replenishment calculation failed to read procurement schedule items for some requested combinations of products and locations.
systemResponse: The replenishment calculation cannot determine an order quantity and thus not create the order plan items for the affected combinations of products and locations. Any comparable order plan items that originate from a previous replenishment run are kept in the system.
procedure: Fix the root cause behind this data-related error and repeat the replenishment calculation. Inspect the low level exceptions attached to this high level exception to retrieve further information about the potential root cause.

messageShortText: Order plan based on unreliable schedule data for product location
diagnosis: The replenishment calculation detected inconsistent or unusual data regarding the procurement schedule. This affects all order plan items for the associated product and receiving location. Depending on the kind of data issue this might also lead to some order plan items not being calculated successfully.
systemResponse: The replenishment calculation attempts to create the order plan items anyway, making assumptions where required. When the calculation of an affected order plan item succeeds, a comparable order plan item that originated from a previous replenishment run is overwritten.
procedure: When the resulting order quantities do not meet your business needs and an urgent action is required, adapt the order quantities in the Review Order Plan Items app. Fix the root cause behind this data-related warning. Inspect the low level exceptions attached to this high level exception to retrieve further information about the potential root cause.

messageShortText: Calculation aborted. Order &1 for delivery &2 has no subsequent delivery
diagnosis: The replenishment calculation failed to calculate an order quantity for order date/time  and delivery date/time  because there is no procurement schedule item after this order.
systemResponse: The replenishment calculation cannot determine an order quantity and thus not create the order plan items for the affected product location for all orders on or after order date/time .
procedure: Expand the procurement schedule by adding procurement schedule items with a later delivery date/time than .

messageShortText: Order quantity based on wrong configuration or unsupported/wrong input
diagnosis: The calculated order quantity is based on some unreliable data. This happens when a step of the replenishment calculation needs to make assumptions regarding its input to be able to proceed.
systemResponse: The replenishment calculation creates the order plan item. Any comparable order plan item that originates from a previous replenishment run is overwritten.
procedure: When the resulting order quantity does not meet your business needs and an urgent action is required adapt the order quantity in the Review Order Plan Items app. Inspect the low level exceptions attached to this high level exception to retrieve further information about the potential root cause. Fix the root cause behind any other data-related warnings that are displayed for this order plan item in the Review Order Plan Items app. If the low level exceptions or any other exceptions generated for this replenishment run do not allow you to find the root cause, please reach out to SAP.

messageShortText: Replenishment calculation aborted. Error or unsupported input
diagnosis: The replenishment calculation failed to calculate order plan items for a portion or the complete procurement schedule. This happens when a technical error occurred, or a calculation step was provided with data that it cannot process. Furthermore, the error is not associated with a specific product and target location.
systemResponse: The replenishment calculation cannot create some of the order plan items.
procedure: Inspect the low level exceptions attached to this high level exception to retrieve further information about the potential root cause. Fix the root cause behind any other data-related errors or warnings that are generated for this replenishment run. To inspect other exceptions that have been detected during this replenishment run you can use the Monitor Exceptions service. Exceptions that cannot be associated with a calculated order plan item are by default assigned to Business Area Replenishment Cause Determination. For further information on how to filter exceptions by Business Area see the Monitor Exceptions section in the application help for SAP Customer Activity Repository. If the low level exceptions or any other exceptions generated for this replenishment run do not allow you to find the root cause, please reach out to SAP.

messageShortText: Unreliable goods receipts data for product location
diagnosis: The replenishment calculation detected inconsistent or unusual data regarding the posted goods receipts. This affects all order plan items for the associated product and receiving location. While this issue does not abort the calculation, depending on other data issues some order plan items might still not be calculated successfully.
systemResponse: The replenishment calculation attempts to create the order plan items anyway, making assumptions on the posted goods receipts where required or neglecting individual posted goods receipts. The posted goods receipts data is used to estimate which batches might be contained in the current stock that differ from each other regarding their end of shelf life. If the calculation of an affected order plan item succeeds, certain order plan items are overwritten. The overwriting applies to order plan items for a particular product location originating from a previous replenishment run and whose order dates and times are at or after the beginning of the planning horizon.
procedure: When the resulting order quantities do not meet your business needs and an urgent action is required, adapt the order quantities in the Review Order Plan Items app. Fix the root cause behind this data-related warning. Inspect the low level exceptions attached to this high level exception to retrieve further information about the potential root cause.

messageShortText: Order quantity &1 &3 is exceptionally high (threshold: &2 &3)
diagnosis: This order plan item was created automatically by a replenishment calculation run. The planned order quantity of the order plan item in base unit is exceptionally high, because it exceeds the threshold value, which is calculated based on order quantities in the order history.
systemResponse: If no action is performed, the order quantity   will be used when the order plan item is transferred to the ERP system for purchase order creation.
procedure: If the order quantity of the proposed candidate does not meet your business needs and urgent action is required, you can use the Review Order Plan Items app to analyze the reasons for the high order quantity and, if necessary, manually edit the order quantity. Under Proposed Candidate -> Stock Projection, you can review the data used as input for the replenishment calculation. Data related to open goods movements (goods issues) or an increase in demand can provide a possible explanation for the exceptionally high order quantity. Under Relevant Candidates, you can also analyze the order quantities of other candidates and evaluate the consequences of selecting a lower order quantity on your overall replenishment strategy. If you determine that the order quantity of the proposed candidate adequately meets your current demand situation, you do not need to edit the order quantity and no further action is necessary.
comments: Example: In some cases, the high order quantity might be the result of a technical issue, for example, during inbound processing of data from the master data system to the Demand Data Foundation (DDF) module. For example, due to an error during inbound processing, stock information might not have been imported to DDF and the system assumes that the stock level is zero (0). Therefore, you need to analyze all exceptions for the order plan item in order to determine and fix the root cause of the high order quantity. In other cases, the order quantity might be especially high in order to meet a specific business scenario such as a product promotion.
referredConfiguration: Exception Profile: Parameters in section "High Order Quantity Exception" - Percentile for Threshold - Interquartile Range Factor for Threshold

messageShortText: Unknown operating times for target location
diagnosis: The replenishment calculation could not determine the operating times. This affects all order plan items for the associated target location. While this issue does not abort the calculation, depending on other data issues some order plan items might still not be calculated successfully.
systemResponse: The replenishment calculation attempts to create the order plan items anyway, assuming the store is open 24 hours every day. This might lead to wrong assumptions regarding the distribution of demand within a day. When the calculation of an affected order plan item succeeds, a comparable order plan item that originated from a previous replenishment run is overwritten.
procedure: When the resulting order quantities do not meet your business needs and an urgent action is required, adapt the order quantities in the Review Order Plan Items app. Fix the root cause of the unknown operating times for the target location. Inspect the low-level exceptions attached to this high level exception to retrieve further information about the potential root cause.

messageShortText: Calculation skipped. Product location is locked by another process
diagnosis: The replenishment calculation failed to set a lock for the product and location. This is to prevent a concurrent modification of the order plan items of this product location by replenishment calculation, Review Order Plan Items app, and order plan processing.
systemResponse: The replenishment calculation cannot determine an order quantity and thus not create the order plan items for the affected combinations of products and locations. All order plan items for the affected product locations originating from a previous replenishment run and whose order dates and times are at or after the beginning of the planning horizon are marked as deleted.
procedure: Currently, the affected combinations of product and receiving locations are already locked by one of the replenishment processes. This may happen for example when another replenishment calculation runs in parallel for the affected product and receiving locations. Try again later. If the problem remains, please contact your administrator.

messageShortText: Unknown demand for product location
diagnosis: The replenishment calculation could not determine the demand. This affects all order plan items for the associated product and receiving location. While this issue does not abort the calculation, depending on other data issues some order plan items might still not be calculated successfully.
systemResponse: The replenishment calculation attempts to create the order plan items anyway, assuming a demand of zero for the overall planning period. When the calculation of an affected order plan item succeeds, certain order plan items are overwritten. The overwriting applies to order plan items for a particular product location originating from a previous replenishment run and whose order dates and times are at or after the beginning of the planning horizon.
procedure: When the resulting order quantities do not meet your business needs and an urgent action is required, adapt the order quantities in the Review Order Plan Items app. Fix the root cause behind this data-related warning. For further information, see the sections Schedule Model and Forecast as well as Monitor, Manage, and Troubleshoot Jobs of the SAP Customer Activity Repository Application Help at https://help.sap.com/viewer/p/CARAB --> <Your Release> --> <Use> --> <Application Help> .

messageShortText: Unreliable schedule data for order plan item
diagnosis: The replenishment calculation detected inconsistent or unusual data regarding the procurement schedule. This affects the associated order plan item.
systemResponse: The replenishment calculation created the order plan item but applied assumptions where required. All order plan items for the affected product location originating from a previous replenishment run and whose order dates and times are at or after the beginning of the planning horizon are marked as deleted.
procedure: Fix the root cause behind this data-related warning. Inspect the low-level exceptions attached to this high level exception to retrieve further information about the potential root cause.

messageShortText: Ratio of additional spoilage to order quantity exceeds threshold &1
diagnosis: This order plan item was created automatically by a replenishment calculation run. The ratio between the additional spoilage caused by this order plan item and its proposed order quantity is exceptionally high because it exceeds the threshold value, which is .
systemResponse: If no action is performed, the proposed order quantity   will be used when the order plan item is transferred to the ERP system for purchase order creation.
procedure: Under Proposed Candidate -> Stock Projection, you can review the data used as input for the replenishment calculation. Data related to open goods movements (goods issues) or to the mean sales forecast can provide a possible explanation for the additional spoilage. Under Relevant Candidates, you can also analyze the order quantities of other candidates and evaluate the consequences of selecting a lower order quantity on your overall replenishment strategy. If the order plan item still adequately meets your current demand situation despite exceeding the threshold value, you do not need to edit the proposed order quantity and no further action is required.

messageShortText: Minimum service level underrun for minimum stock. Target &1% actual &2%
diagnosis: No order candidate fulfills the constraint regarding the configured minimum service level for minimum stock constraint because no order candidate has a higher service level for minimum stock than percent. The replenishment calculation has determined an order quantity that yields a service level for minimum stock of  percent.
systemResponse: The replenishment calculation selects an order quantity based on other defined constraints and the configured cost model.
procedure: When the resulting order quantity does not meet your business needs and an urgent action is required adapt the order quantity in the Review Order Plan Items app. Fix the root cause behind any data-related warnings that are displayed for this order plan item in the Review Order Plan Items app. Analyze why the replenishment calculation selects an order quantity that does not fulfil the defined constraint for service level for minimum stock. This can have two reasons: •There is no potential order quantity which fulfils the minimum service level for minimum stock. This can happen if, for example, the shelf life of the product is shorter than the demand period. In this case, consider a change in the procurement schedule. •There are other constraints which are in conflict with the minimum service level for minimum stock and have a higher rank. In this case, changing the procurement schedule towards shorter demand periods can help to reduce the order quantities required to fulfil the minimum service level for minimum stock. The resulting lower order quantities are more likely to fulfil any conflicting maximum constraint. Alternatively, you can resolve the situation by changing the constraint definition using the Manage Constraint Profiles app. In both cases, it is helpful to use the Simulate Replenishment app for finding an appropriate configuration of the procument schedule and the constraints.

messageShortText: Maximum service level overrun at end of listing. Target &1% actual &2%
diagnosis: No order candidate fulfills the constraint regarding the configured maximum service level at end of listing constraint, because no order candidate has a lower service level at end of listing  than percent. The replenishment calculation has chosen an order quantity that yields a service level at end of listing of  percent.
systemResponse: The replenishment calculation selects an order quantity based on other defined constraints and the configured cost model.
procedure: If the resulting order quantity does not meet your business needs and an urgent action is required, adapt the order quantity in the Review Order Plan Items app. Fix the root cause behind any data-related warnings that are displayed for this order plan item in the Review Order Plan Items app. The replenishment calculation only determines an order quantity that fulfills a maximum service level at end of listing if the remaining stock is not too high at the end of the current listing period. Therefore, consider the following: •Use the Simulate Replenishment app to find unusual quantities within the timeseries of different KPIs. •Configure the replenishment calculation in a way that avoids high quantities of stock. •A high service level at end of listing might also be caused by a high current stock. In this case, there is no chance to avoid the situation by adjusting the replenishment calculation.

messageShortText: Order quantity based on missing parameter profile assignment(s)
diagnosis: The calculated order quantity is based on one or more missing parameter profile assignments. This happens when a step of the replenishment calculation needs to make assumptions regarding the configuration parameters stored in one or more parameter profiles.
systemResponse: The replenishment calculation creates the order plan item. All order plan items for the affected product location originating from a previous replenishment run and whose order dates and times are at or after the beginning of the planning horizon are marked as deleted.
procedure: When the resulting order quantity does not meet your business needs and an urgent action is required adapt the order quantity in the Review Order Plan Items app. Inspect the low level exceptions attached to this high level exception to retrieve further information about the potential root cause. Identify the missing parameter assignment(s) by inspecting the attached low-level message(s). For further information regarding profile definition and assignment, see the Configure Your Solution section in the application help for SAP Replenishment Planning.

messageShortText: No order plan items generated. End of order plan horizon unknown.
diagnosis: The replenishment calculation failed to determine the end date/time of the order plan horizon for the product and receiving location.
systemResponse: The replenishment calculation cannot create the order plan items for the affected product location.
procedure: Fix the root cause behind this data-related error by either setting the end date/time of the order plan horizon in the Order Date/Time to field within the Calculate Replenishment report or maintaining the horizon parameters in the Manage Configuration Assignments app.

messageShortText: Candidate determination failed. Error code &1
Candidate determination failed. Error code &1 context &2 / &3 / &4
Candidate determination failed. Technical error: &1&2&3&4
Warning with code &1 during candidate determination
Warning with code &1 during candidate determination. Context &2 / &3 / &4
Missing mandatory configuration parameter: &1

messageShortText: Availability date/time &1 of order before stock date/time &2
Schedule not supported. Reason code &1 dates and times &2 / &3
diagnosis: The order candidate determination does not support the affected procurement schedule item. The two specified dates/times are in the wrong order. This could be a pair of order dates/times, delivery dates/times, or availability dates/times.
systemResponse: The replenishment calculation cannot create order candidates.
procedure: Adapt the procurement schedule or contact SAP for further assistance. The following reason codes provide further information why the procurement schedule could not be processed: •Reason code 24:  For consecutive orders the order date time of a subsequent order is earlier •Reason code 25:  For consecutive orders the delivery date time of a subsequent order is earlier •Reason code 26:  For consecutive orders the availability date time of a subsequent order is earlier

messageShortText: No constraint defined for any KPI. Set of order candidates not reliable
Negative stock batch present. Stock quantity &1 Shelf life end &2
No subsequent delivery date/time after current order
Stock quantity &1 not supported. &1 contains non-zero decimal places
comments: No order will be calculated!!! The stock is not rounded nor the decimal part of the stock is ignored.

messageShortText: Quantity of open goods movement (&1) not supported
diagnosis: The order candidate determination does not support the quantity of the open goods movement as it contains non-zero decimal places.
systemResponse: The replenishment calculation cannot create order plan item candidates.
procedure: Adapt the quantity of the open goods movement so that it contains no decimal places or only decimal places that are equal to zero. Alternatively, contact SAP for further assistance.

messageShortText: Order quantity based on unassigned cost profile
diagnosis: The required cost profile is not assigned to the given product location.
systemResponse: The replenishment calculation creates the order plan item. All order plan items for the associated product location originating from a previous replenishment run and whose order dates and times are at or after the beginning of the planning horizon are marked as deleted. The calculated order quantity is based on cost profile parameters whose values are assumed to be 0 (resulting in overall costs of 0).
procedure: Assign a cost profile to the respective product location on the desired assignment level. If the cost profile to be assigned does not yet exist, create a cost profile in the Manage Cost Profiles app. After the missing cost profile has been created, use the Manage Configuration Assignments app to assign the profile to the product location. For further information regarding profile definition and assignment, see the Configure Your Solution section in the application help for SAP Replenishment Planning.

messageShortText: Order quantity based on unassigned constraint profile
diagnosis: The required constraint profile is not assigned to the given product location.
systemResponse: The replenishment calculation creates the order plan item. All order plan items for the associated product location originating from a previous replenishment run and whose order dates and times are at or after the beginning of the planning horizon are marked as deleted. The calculated order quantity was determined without constraints.
procedure: Assign a constraint profile to the respective product location on the desired assignment level. If the constraint profile to be assigned does not yet exist, create a constraint profile in the Manage Constraint Profiles app. After the missing constraint profile has been created, use the Manage Configuration Assignments app to assign the profile to the product location. For further information regarding profile definition and assignment, see the Configure Your Solution section in the application help for SAP Replenishment Planning.

messageShortText: Order quantity based on unassigned shelf cost profile
diagnosis: The required shelf cost profile is not assigned to the given product location.
systemResponse: The replenishment calculation creates the order plan item. All order plan items for the associated product location originating from a previous replenishment run and whose order dates and times are at or after the beginning of the planning horizon are marked as deleted. The calculated order quantity is based on a shelf capacity violation cost of 0.
procedure: Assign a shelf cost profile to the respective product location on the desired assignment level. If the shelf cost profile to be assigned does not yet exist, create a shelf cost profile in the Manage Shelf Cost Profiles app. After the missing shelf cost profile has been created, use the Manage Configuration Assignments app to assign the profile to the product location. For further information regarding profile definition and assignment, see the Configure Your Solution section in the application help for SAP Replenishment Planning.
referredConfiguration: Manage Configuration Assignments: Shelf Cost Profile

messageShortText: Order quantity based on unassigned exception profile
diagnosis: The required exception profile is not assigned to the given product location.
systemResponse: The replenishment calculation creates the order plan item. All order plan items for the associated product location originating from a previous replenishment run and whose order dates and times are at or after the beginning of the planning horizon are marked as deleted. It is not possible to detect exceptional situations like a high order quantity or a high spoilage.
procedure: Assign an exception profile to the respective product location on the desired assignment level. If the exception profile to be assigned does not yet exist, create an exception profile in the Manage Exception Profiles app. After the missing exception profile has been created, use the Manage Configuration Assignments app to assign the profile to the product location. For further information regarding profile definition and assignment, see the Configure Your Solution section in the application help for SAP Replenishment Planning.
